title: Nenad N. Cvetković
text:
Nenad Cvetković (; born 6 January 1996) is a <a href="Serbia">Serbia</a>n <a href="Association%20football">football</a>er, playing for <a href="F.C.%20Ashdod">F.C. Ashdod</a>.
Club career.
Born in <a href="U%C5%BEice">Užice</a>, Cvetković came throw the <a href="Red%20Star%20Belgrade">Red Star Belgrade</a> youth categories. In summer 2014, he moved on loan to <a href="Serbian%20League%20Belgrade">Serbian League Belgrade</a> side <a href="FK%20IM%20Rakovica">IM Rakovica</a> where he spent the first half-season. After he overgrown youth team, Cvetković signed his first three-year professional contract with Red Star, being licensed with the first team in qualifications for the <a href="2015%E2%80%9316%20UEFA%20Europa%20League">2015–16 UEFA Europa League</a>. Cvetković was also loaned to <a href="FK%20Radni%C4%8Dki%20Beograd">Radnički Beograd</a> for the 2015–16 season in the Serbian League Belgrade.
At the beginning of 2016, Cvetković signed with <a href="Serbian%20First%20League">Serbian First League</a> club <a href="FK%20Zemun">Zemun</a>.
On 27 July 2020 signed in the <a href="Israeli%20Premier%20League">Israeli Premier League</a> club <a href="F.C.%20Ashdod">F.C. Ashdod</a>.
